7.22	Sir_Philip_Green	Philip Green	Sir Philip Green (born 15 March 1952) is a British businessman. Green was born into a Jewish family in 1952, beginning as a businessman at the age of 15. The first and last quoted company Green took lead of was "Amber Day", from which he stepped down as CEO and Chairman in 1992. Since then he has had links to a range of British companies; including a hostile bid for Marks and Spencer and the management of the Arcadia Group, both alongside or supporting his wife. He has been involved in a range of controversies related to both his personal and business life.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b0/Philip_Green.jpg/200px-Philip_Green.jpg
